# Your fleet

You control a fleet of remote machines. You reach all of them with the `fleet`
command (run it via your shell tool). There are **no other network endpoints** —
shell and GUI both go over SSH. You never handle SSH keys, hosts, or ports
yourself; `fleet` and your config already have them.

## Targets
<!-- rendered by the operator from the fleet manifest -->
| name  | kind     | os      | use it for                          |
|-------|----------|---------|-------------------------------------|
| web1  | terminal | linux   | shell, files, running programs      |
| desk1 | gui      | linux   | desktop apps, browser, clicking     |
| win1  | gui      | windows | Windows desktop apps                 |

## Terminal targets — run commands
```
fleet run  <name> <command...>      # e.g. fleet run web1 ls -la /srv
fleet push <name> <local> <remote>  # copy a file up
fleet pull <name> <remote> <local>  # copy a file down
```

## GUI targets — see and act on the desktop
A GUI target also accepts everything above (it has a shell), PLUS screen control.
**Loop: screenshot → read it → act → screenshot again to confirm.** Coordinates
are screen pixels (top-left origin).

```
fleet screenshot <name> <out.png>   # capture the screen to a file, then VIEW it
fleet gui <name> click  <x> <y>     # left click
fleet gui <name> rclick <x> <y>     # right click
fleet gui <name> dclick <x> <y>     # double click
fleet gui <name> move   <x> <y>     # move cursor
fleet gui <name> scroll <dx> <dy>   # scroll
fleet gui <name> type  "text"       # type text
fleet gui <name> key   <keyname>    # press one key (e.g. Return, Tab, Escape)
fleet gui <name> hotkey ctrl l      # press a key combo (each key a separate arg)
```
Action calls reply `{"success":true}` (or an error); `fleet screenshot` writes a PNG.

Typical step:
```
fleet screenshot desk1 /tmp/s.png    # then view /tmp/s.png to locate the target
fleet gui desk1 click 740 410        # click it
fleet screenshot desk1 /tmp/s.png    # confirm the result
```

## Running an app in the background
The GUI targets have a live logged-in desktop session. Launch apps non-blocking,
then drive them by screenshot:
```
fleet run desk1 'DISPLAY=:0 nohup firefox >/dev/null 2>&1 &'   # linux
fleet run win1  'start "" msedge'                              # windows
```
Give the app a moment to appear, then screenshot before clicking.

## Notes
- Always screenshot **after** an action to verify it landed — do not assume.
- If a click misses, re-screenshot and recompute coordinates; the layout may have
  shifted or scrolled.
- Connections are kept warm automatically; you don't need to connect/disconnect.
